title: [Western Waterway, Charl's Teeth]
description: In the shadowed nooks and crevices of a particularly high and craggy set of rocks rising proudly from the ocean's depths, seagulls sleep peacefully within their rookery.  The sound of the waves crashing against the teeth-like sentinels echoes loudly as the current churns, but unfortunately not even the strong scent of the sea can subdue the ammoniac smell of the guano left by the seagulls.
paths: Obvious paths: northeast, east, south, southwest
